{
  "texts": [
    "We observed that GPT-4 handles longer input sizes (3000 tokens) effectively, often outperforming its handling of shorter input sizes (1500 tokens).",
    "This is particularly evident with prompt 4, where GPT-4 achieved an F1 Score of 0.941 and precision of 1.000 at an input size of 3000, suggesting a remarkable ability to maintain high precision with increased input length.",
    "Next, we used a single label/example for the one-shot approach.",
    "The prompt accompanying this label/example was similar to the prompt 4 in the zero-shot approach, as it yielded better results.",
    "An input size of 1500 tokens for each combination, resulted in an F1 score of 0.228 for GPT-3.5 Turbo and 0.824 for GPT-4."
  ]
}